2022 is the 50th anniversary of the normalization of diplomatic relations between China and Japan. Last Friday, the U.S. and Japan held a virtual 2+2 meeting and said China was undermining the rules-based international order. Japan is opposing China on multiple fronts and forming alliances against China but at the same time wants to maintain strong ties, as many Japanese companies are economically dependent on China. In this episode of BizBeat, CGTN's Michelle Van den Bergh explains why Japan should stop "double-dealing".